<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,399,654]" box="[151,573,399,426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,399,425]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Description.</emphasis>
Length. Male 
<quantity box="[475,569,400,426]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,399,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[197,334,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Coloration.</emphasis>
Pale brown with dark brown spots. Anteclypeus dark brown in apical half. Pronoutm (
<figureCitation box="[1365,1436,437,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[1421,1436,437,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D) darker than head. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[574,641,474,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[630,641,474,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) with central area darker than lateral and caudal areas. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,795,819]" captionTargetBox="[269,1324,200,761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[262,1324,184,774]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pedionis dorsal and lateral habitus. A &amp; B, Pedionis (Pedionis) lii sp. nov.; C &amp; D, Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195496/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,228,512,538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D) brownish with apical areas of claval vein, apex of clavus and irregular spot near apex of corium, dark brown; venation dark brown with white spots. Legs brown with paler markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,399,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[197,350,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Morphology.</emphasis>
Body comparatively slender and small. Clypeus expanded; anteclypeus tapered. Pronotum as long as scutellum. 
<collectingCountry box="[402,461,624,650]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibial spinulation R 
<number box="[693,701,640,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[708,738,624,650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="11.0">11</number>
, R 
<number box="[771,779,640,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[786,803,624,650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="9.0">9</number>
, R 
<number box="[835,843,640,654]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[850,867,624,650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195500/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" targetBox="[284,1316,716,1775]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1814,1901]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1814,1838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[288,577,1815,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pedionis">
<emphasis box="[288,577,1815,1838]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Pedionis 
<taxonomicName box="[382,577,1815,1838]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="spinata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Pedionis">(Pedionis) spinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,667,1814,1837]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, pygophore, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1942,2006]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[197,386,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[544,617,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[284,1316,716,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[249,1338,706,1792]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov. A, pygophore, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195500/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number box="[603,617,1942,1968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A) without caudo-dorsal spine usually found in 
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1319,1943,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1319,1943,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Pedionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, setae on ventral margin relatively stout. Subgenital plate, style and connective similar to that in 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1304,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garuda">
<emphasis box="[1189,1304,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">P. garuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1814,1838]" captionTargetBox="[284,1316,716,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[249,1338,706,1792]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pedionis (Pedionis) spinata sp. nov. A, pygophore, subgenital plates and valve, lateral view; B, style, lateral view; C, aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus and dorsal connective, caudal view; E, connective, lateral view; F, connective, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195500/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Figs. 
<number box="[228,243,152,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D) shaft with triangular lobe-like projection on dorsal margin, with subapical lateral expansion ventro-posterior view, with pair of small spine-like processes subapically; dorsal connective simple, distal part curved with marginal serrations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" box="[197,422,264,290]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis box="[197,293,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
