<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,413,439]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[328,529,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinata">
<emphasis box="[328,529,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Pedionis spinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" authorityName="Huang &amp; Viraktamath" box="[666,1137,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscutellata">
<emphasis box="[666,862,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">P. rufoscutellata</emphasis>
Huang &amp; Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
externally, but differs in having the posterior margin of the pygophore truncate apically without a ventral process; and subapical margin of the aedeagal shaft with a large triangular expansion along the ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1138,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,551]" box="[197,1138,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,525,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
